  <span id="freeText2032020922971453400" style="display:none">What would you do if you could foresee your death? Would you embrace it willingly or go back and change the path of your life? Do you have regrets that you would alter, if you had the option?<br /><br />This is Anaya's story. She is a 35 year-old doctor who upon her death is given a chance to travel back in time and re-live her life. She chooses to travel back to her teenage years when she dropped out of college. She wants to make different choices from the ones she made first time around. She wants a second chance with her family especially her bipolar father and also the chance to prevent her friend's death.<br /><br />But what is the impact of changing the course of your life? Is every consequence controllable and predictable?<br /><br />This is an interesting and poignant read. Anaya is relate-able. I found myself examining her decisions and how each action had brought her to where she was.<br /><br />The audio narrator is fantastic and her voice drew me easily into the story and held me there until the last word.<br /><br />A wonderful and highly recommended listen.</span>
