    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2391728905" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2391728905" />
    <a title="Rachel Kester" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38583874-rachel-kester"><img alt="Rachel Kester" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493940399p2/38583874.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2391728905?book_show_action=true">May 14, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rachel Kester" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rachel Kester" href="/user/show/38583874-rachel-kester">Rachel Kester</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2391728905" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17254515205424575821">The Watchmaker’s Doctor is a novel by G.M.T. Schuilling that tells the tale of a young doctor who is caring for an older man at a retirement center. This man knows a massive secret about his doctor’s life, that she is about to die, and as a former watchmaker, works to create a clock that can work to turn back time before this horrible event occurs. However, the catch is that she must turn the clock back to a specific time in her life and redo something that she regretted doing.<br/><br/>This novel is a un</span>
  <span id="freeText17254515205424575821" style="display:none">The Watchmaker’s Doctor is a novel by G.M.T. Schuilling that tells the tale of a young doctor who is caring for an older man at a retirement center. This man knows a massive secret about his doctor’s life, that she is about to die, and as a former watchmaker, works to create a clock that can work to turn back time before this horrible event occurs. However, the catch is that she must turn the clock back to a specific time in her life and redo something that she regretted doing.<br /><br />This novel is a unique and creative tale that will have you on the edge of your seat. Schuilling’s writing style is captivating which helps to make the story even more interesting. At 101 pages, it’s not necessarily that long of a read, so it’s perfect for those looking for a good book that isn’t too time-consuming. If you enjoy stories about time traveling or science fiction, you should definitely check this book out.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17254515205424575821" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

